Description: Round-topped limestone stela sculptured with the winged sun-disc with pendent uraei at the top; below is a twenty-seven line Greek text containing a decree passed by the people of Busiris in honour of Tiberius Claudius Balbillus, praefect of Egypt 55-59 AD under Nero; above the main inscription is a graffito.
Findspot: Found/Acquired: Egypt, excavated near the sphinx at Giza
Bibliographic references: Inscription / The Collection of Ancient Greek Inscriptions in the British Museum (1067)
Associated names: Named in inscription: Tiberius Claudius Balbillus
